history.content:
http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml doesn't say what you suggest.  Most of the students currently enrolled are undeclared L&S students.  There are spots held for EECS/COE undeclared majors "Until the end of undergraduate Phase II appointments ."  They will continue to be held.

We will try to expand the class to be able to accommodate other interested students especially undeclared first and second year students as well as new undeclared transfer students.

I'm an intended CS major, and I've currently been waitlisted for 61B. According to this link: http://www.eecs.berkeley.edu/Policies/enrollment.shtml, LSCS intended majors receive priority once 300 seats have been filled by EECS and COE undeclared majors. There are 213 people enrolled in 61B as of now.

Does that mean that once another 87 people from EECS and COE sign up, the waitlist will be automatically processed to allow intended CS majors to enroll?
history.subject: 61B Enrollment
